
[1]canonization

   CANONIZATION, n. [See Canonize.]

   1. The act of declaring a man a saint, or rather the act of ranking a
   deceased person in the catalogue of saints, called a canon. This act is
   preceded by beatification, and by an examination into the life and
   miracles of the person; after which the Pope decrees the canonization.

   2. The state of being sainted.
